Comment: From when I started to play 1.d4 openings my ELO rating went up with 150 points about. I think 1.d4 brings to White a very solid position with very good attacking chances. Now my favourites are Colle system and Torre attack. I'm not good in QGambit but play it often. I want to learn more about it and about Catalan opening

This is a turns-the-game moment. Black tries to break the weaker white-side, considering  defence position itself is solid. Now White has some variants more of which would bring weakness at queenside mainly because of not castling. The capturing of b5 inevitably will lead to opened a-line or c-pawn march. Rb1 will save the position for a little
